# MetaMask Design System - Color Tokens

This document defines the official color tokens for the MetaMask design system. All components must use these tokens for consistent theming.

## Usage

Always use design tokens for colors. Never use raw hex values directly.

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
const c = useColors();
style={{ backgroundColor: c.background.section }}
style={{ color: c.text.default }}
style={{ borderColor: c.border.muted }}

// ❌ Incorrect
style={{ backgroundColor: '#31333A' }}
style={{ color: '#FFFFFF' }}
```

## Color Hook

Use the `useColors()` hook to access theme-aware colors:

```tsx
import { useColors } from "@/lib/components";

function MyComponent() {
  const c = useColors();
  
  return (
    <div style={{ 
      backgroundColor: c.background.section,
      color: c.text.default 
    }}>
      Content
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Dark Theme Colors (Default)

### Backgrounds

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `background.default` | #222325 | Main app background |
| `background.alternative` | #121314 | Sunken areas, modals backdrop |
| `background.section` | #31333A | Cards, elevated surfaces |
| `background.subsection` | #3D4049 | Nested containers |
| `background.muted` | #474951 | Subtle backgrounds, disabled states |
| `background.hover` | #3D4049 | Interactive hover state |
| `background.pressed` | #474951 | Interactive pressed state |

### Text

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `text.default` | #FFFFFF | Primary text, headings |
| `text.alternative` | #858B9A | Secondary text, descriptions |
| `text.muted` | #686E7D | Disabled text, placeholders |

